Alternate Contact: David Purdon, Assistant Executive Director; Email: david@cofoodbank.com
Service Details: - Provides program specially designed to meet the nutritional needs of pregnant mothers and families with children under the age of one- Participants are eligible for a weekly hamper containing milk, eggs, fresh fruits, vegetables and baby basics, with mothers also receiving a one-time layette containing new baby items when their baby is born- Public health nurses are available at the Food Bank twice per month to answer any questions new moms may have
Hours: Kelowna Office Hours: Mon-Fri: 8:00am - 4:00pm West Kelowna Office Hours: Mon-Fri: 8:00am - 3:00pm
Eligibility: Pregnant mothers and families with children under the age of one
How to Apply: Please visit the website, email or phone for additional information on applying for the Tiny Bundles Program
